<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>address oneself to someone • address someone</xh5><p> <i>address oneself to someone—</i>speak or appeal to a person: He came into the room, and <u>addressed himself to me</u> with the best grace in the world.</p><p> <i>address someone—</i>1. <i>= address oneself to someone:</i> The Education Secretary had to <u>address</u> a hostile crowd of teachers. 2. speak to a person using a nickname or a title: Don’t <u>address</u> me as “Colonel”; I’m only a major.</p> </entry>
